fields.description:
Inside the issue tracker, lists are formatted with way to much margin around them. It looks much better in the wiki. To work around this, I&#x27;m using the following Custom CSS:

{code}
.wiki-content ul {
   margin-top: 10px;
   margin-bottom: 10px;
   padding-left: 30px;
}

.wiki-content ul ul {
   margin-top: 3px;
   margin-bottom: 3px;
   padding-left: 20px;
}

.wiki-content li {
   margin-top: 0px;
   margin-bottom: 0px;
}

#issue-main-content .metadata {
   font-size: 12px;
   color: BCLOUD-707070;
   margin-top: 0;
   margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.issues-list .date {
   display: none;
}
{code}

This makes the metadata line below the issue title a bit less prominent and provides some space between it and the main content.

When pushing over https, users may see an error similar to the following:

{code}
#!bash

The requested URL returned error: 403 while accessing https://{username}@bitbucket.org/{username}/{repo slug}.git/info/refs
fatal: HTTP request failed
{code}

This is a bug. Instead the message should tell users that the account they are trying to push to is over their plan limit.

When previewing this issue description, the following line

Here is an example of *bold* in an issue.

renders "bold in bold, but appears as:

{code}
Here is an example of
bold
in an issue.
{code}

This is a CSS issue where {{strong}} elements are having {{display: block;}} set by the following stylesheet:

[https://dwz7u9t8u8usb.cloudfront.net/m/41d49ff119d6/compressed/css/25ec0da2bbe9.css|https://dwz7u9t8u8usb.cloudfront.net/m/41d49ff119d6/compressed/css/25ec0da2bbe9.css]

{code}
/* for headings in form descriptions */
form.aui .field-group strong {
  display: block;
}
{code}

which is getting applied to elements in the preview form.  The final text renders properly, but it makes previewing bold elements a paint.  (Also applies to previewing comment text.)
